  "prompt": "Who pays for the cars on Top Gear?",
  "response": "On \"Top Gear,\" the cars featured in the show are typically provided by manufacturers for review and showcasing purposes. The BBC, the network that produces \"Top Gear,\" does not buy the cars outright. Instead, car manufacturers often supply vehicles for a limited time, which allows them to promote their models to a large audience. In some cases, the show may also procure vehicles through rental or leasing agreements, especially for specific segments or stunts. However, the production team generally does not own the cars permanently.",
